                                           owl:allValuesFrom rope:StaticSection
                                         ] ;
                         rdfs:comment "Note: other service types (customs, track assignment) rather relate to the Train run."@en ,
                                      "Train servicing process, e.g. maintenance, brake inspection..."@en ;
                         rdfs:label "Train servicing state"@en .


###  https://cdm.ovh/rsm/operations/rope/rope#TrainSpeedState
rope:TrainSpeedState rdf:type owl:Class ;
                     rdfs:subClassOf rope:TrainState ;
                     rdfs:label "Train speed state"@en .


###  https://cdm.ovh/rsm/operations/rope/rope#TrainState
rope:TrainState rdf:type owl:Class ;
                rdfs:subClassOf rope:OperationalState ,
                                [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                  owl:onProperty dul:hasParticipant ;
                                  owl:someValuesFrom rope:Train
                                ] ;
                rdfs:comment """Characterizes the state of the Train (as a physical asset), e.g. speed, mass, GPS coordinates of some particular point of the train, etc.
Since the subclasses are not disjoint, the ontology user is free to use a single individual to combine information. Ultimately, most useful combinations should give rise to dedicated subclasses, in the interest of efficient data serialization and transformation to/from document formats such as JSON or XML."""@en ;
                rdfs:label "Train state"@en .


###  https://cdm.ovh/rsm/operations/rope/rope#TransportCollaborationMessage
rope:TransportCollaborationMessage rdf:type owl:Class ;
